{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:27:36.275238+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: e460887e6e08f3b03d5bc7a0c902fbc6dcf176c2)", "id": "lc_bb9ae576-8e6a-42b0-8dc5-5625c6de44a7"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\"\"\"Command-line entry point for gwc.\"\"\"\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport argparse\nimport sys\n\nfrom . import git_ops\nfrom .config import load_config\n\n\ndef build_parser() -> argparse.ArgumentParser:\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(prog=\"gwc\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--version\", action=\"version\", version=\"gwc 0.1.0\")\n    subparsers = parser.add_subparsers(dest=\"command\", required=True)\n\n    subparsers.add_parser(\n        \"status-summary\",\n        help=\"Print a one-line summary of the current branch state.\",\n    )\n\n    p_branch = subparsers.add_parser(\n        \"branch-name\",\n        help=\"Generate a conventional branch name for an issue.\",\n    )\n    p_branch.add_argument(\"issue_number\", type=int)\n    p_branch.add_argument(\"slug\", type=str)\n\n    p_clean = subparsers.add_parser(\n        \"clean-merged\",\n        help=\"List or delete local branches fully merged into main.\",\n    )\n    p_clean.add_argument(\n        \"--apply\",\n        action=\"store_true\",\n        default=False,\n        help=\"Actually delete branches (default is dry-run).\",\n    )\n\n    return parser\n\n\ndef main(argv: list[str] | None = None) -> int:\n    parser = build_parser()\n    args = parser.parse_args(argv)\n    config = load_config()\n\n    if args.command == \"status-summary\":\n        print(git_ops.status_summary())\n        return 0\n\n    if args.command == \"branch-name\":\n        prefix = config.get(\"branch_name\", {}).get(\"prefix\", \"issue-\")\n        print(f\"{prefix}{args.issue_number}-{args.slug}\")\n        return 0\n\n    if args.command == \"clean-merged\":\n        protected = config.get(\"clean_merged\", {}).get(\n            \"protected_branches\", [\"main\", \"develop\"]\n        )\n        merged = git_ops.list_merged_branches(protected=protected)\n        if not merged:\n            print(\"No merged branches to delete.\")\n            return 0\n        if args.apply:\n            for b in merged:\n                git_ops.delete_branch(b)\n            print(f\"Deleted: {', '.join(merged)}\")\n        else:\n            print(f\"Would delete: {', '.join(merged)}\")\n        return 0\n\n    parser.error(f\"unknown command: {args.command}\")\n    return 2\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    sys.exit(main())\n", "id": "lc_ef9210cb-6609-4986-a8e7-6d1ec9ae3185"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "33d678db-dc0f-4bdd-894d-cde5fe5148d3", "tool_call_id": "call_77fc660ef9ac45c4a87bcb24", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:27:43.410340+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Here's what I found:\n\n## Command-line tool: `gwc`\n\nThe package installs a CLI tool called **`gwc`** (short for \"Git Workflow Companion\").\n\nThis is defined in `pyproject.toml`:\n```\n[project.scripts]\ngwc = \"gwc.cli:main\"\n```\n\n### What does `gwc` currently do?\n\nThe tool has **three subcommands**:\n\n1. **`gwc status-summary`** — Prints a one-line summary of the current branch state (delegates to `git_ops.status_summary()`).\n\n2. **`gwc branch-name <issue_number> <slug>`** — Generates a conventional branch name for an issue. By default it produces something like `issue-42-fix-login-bug` (using a configurable prefix, default `\"issue-\"`).\n\n3. **`gwc clean-merged [--apply]`** — Lists (or optionally deletes) local branches that are fully merged into main. By default it's a **dry-run** (just prints what *would* be deleted). Pass `--apply` to actually delete the branches. Protected branches (`main`, `develop` by default, configurable) are excluded.\n\nAll three subcommands read optional configuration from a config file (via `gwc.config.load_config()`), and the git operations are handled by `gwc.git_ops`.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 296, "prompt_tokens": 4170, "total_tokens": 4466, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 12, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 3520, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.000552942, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.000295422, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00025752}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780864056-hUNxxWMojZnP7EPmTsRs", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3c4-fbd3-7a52-ac21-929db9fd7cb3-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 4170, "output_tokens": 296, "total_tokens": 4466, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 3520}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 12}}}}]}}}
